  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic pain self-management skills can help patients improve daily functioning and quality
      of life. The goal of this study is to evaluate chronic pain self-managed Integrative Yoga
      Therapy intervention delivered in a sample of 25 older adults recruited from community site
      in Leicester.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
